Bring a large pot of water to a boil; season with salt. Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add onions and sweat gently for about 10 minutes. Add tomatoes and simmer for 5 to 8 minutes. Cook pasta according to package directions. Drain pasta. Toss pasta with tomato sauce and thyme for 1 minute. Season with salt and pepper. Sprinkle with freshly grated Parmigiano-Reggiano cheese and serve immediately.